05:08.508 --> 05:11.743
Hope he's okay.

05:11.745 --> 05:15.480
I never thought I'd have a boss
better than your brother,

05:15.482 --> 05:17.482
But walden is good people.

05:17.484 --> 05:19.618
He's the best.

05:19.620 --> 05:22.487
The guy has the biggest heart
of anyone I have ever met.

05:22.489 --> 05:24.456
Yep, a heart of gold.

05:24.458 --> 05:27.426
Clogged with arterial plaque.

05:27.428 --> 05:29.361
You've been a good
friend to walden.

05:29.363 --> 05:30.462
He's lucky
to have you.

05:30.464 --> 05:34.466
He's lucky to have you,
too, sister berta.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.468
And, listen, um...

05:36.470 --> 05:40.205
If, god forbid,
the worst happens,

05:40.207 --> 05:42.374
I-I just want you
to know that, uh...

05:42.376 --> 05:45.143
You'll always have
a job at the house.

05:45.145 --> 05:48.146
I mean, we'd have to talk
reduced salaries, but, uh...

05:48.148 --> 05:50.549
What makes you think
he'd leave you the house?

05:50.551 --> 05:52.117
I'm his best friend.

05:52.119 --> 05:53.618
There's nobody closer
to him than me.

05:53.620 --> 05:55.220
I clean his underwear.

05:55.222 --> 05:56.521
I <i>wear</i> his underwear.

05:56.523 --> 05:58.323
(laughs)

05:58.325 --> 05:59.991
Alan harper?

05:59.993 --> 06:01.793
Oh, oh, that's me.

06:01.795 --> 06:03.662
I'm dr. Prajneep.

06:03.664 --> 06:05.464
Your friend had a
mild heart attack.

06:05.466 --> 06:07.299
We put in a stent to
clear the blockage.

06:07.301 --> 06:08.066
Is that bad?

06:08.068 --> 06:09.634
In general,

06:09.636 --> 06:11.036
A heart attack is bad.

06:11.038 --> 06:13.205
But, uh, he should
make a full recovery.

06:13.207 --> 06:14.573
Oh, thank god.

06:14.575 --> 06:15.741
Oh, that is
a huge relief.

06:15.743 --> 06:17.642
Um, is there anything
we should do at home?

06:17.644 --> 06:20.479
I just want to make sure
he has all the care he needs.

06:20.481 --> 06:22.581
Uh, any special diet,
exercises, medications?

06:22.583 --> 06:23.982
If it'd help,

06:23.984 --> 06:26.551
