right back to the freezer.

09:29.937 --> 09:31.503
You know, it just goes to show,

09:31.505 --> 09:33.271
Your life can end
in the blink of an eye.

09:33.273 --> 09:35.106
One day you're here,
the next day you're gone.

09:35.108 --> 09:36.775
That's why I live
by the philosophy

09:36.777 --> 09:39.411
"one day I'm here,
the next day I'm still here."

09:39.413 --> 09:43.682
You know, if-if I would have
died, who would have missed me?

09:43.684 --> 09:46.384
What are you talking about?
I would, berta would.

09:46.386 --> 09:48.920
A-and you just got an e-mail
from netflix the other day

09:48.922 --> 09:50.989
That literally said,
"we miss you."

09:52.858 --> 09:56.461
You know, other than you guys
and my mom, I got nobody.

09:56.463 --> 09:58.029
At least you got jake.

09:58.031 --> 10:00.231
Well, that's true.

10:00.233 --> 10:02.400
I'll always have
my little guy.

10:02.402 --> 10:04.269
Although, in his last e-mail,

10:04.271 --> 10:07.472
He, uh, asked me when the
fourth of July was this year.

10:09.875 --> 10:12.410
But, yes, I'm very lucky.

10:12.412 --> 10:15.947
Do you know how much
I would give to have a kid

10:15.949 --> 10:18.550
Who didn't understand
the concept of a calendar?

10:20.252 --> 10:22.053
All I have is money.

10:22.055 --> 10:23.655
Yeah.

10:23.657 --> 10:26.524
'cause I wouldn't give up jake
for a billion dollars.

10:29.328 --> 10:31.329
I got to make some changes.

10:31.331 --> 10:32.564
Changes are good.

10:32.566 --> 10:34.165
Uh, you know,
I remember when I switched

10:34.167 --> 10:36.034
From <i>american idol</i> to <i>the voice.</i>

10:37.069 --> 10:38.470
My life turned around

10:38.472 --> 10:40.972
Like blake shelton's chair.

10:40.974 --> 10:42.641
You know what?

10:42.643 --> 10:44.776
I want to have a kid of my own.

10:44.778 --> 10:46.578
What?

10:46.580 --> 10:48.947
Yeah, I want something
to give my life meaning.

10:48.949 --> 10:51.650
I want somebody
I can love unconditionally.

10:51.652 --> 10:53.952
Someone I can teach,
someone I can nurture,

10:53.954 --> 10:55.987
Someone I can leave
all this to.

10:55.989 --> 10:57.155
Well...

10:57.157 --> 11:00.792
I mean, I don't know
what to say, except...

11:00.794 --> 11:02.627
Papa?

11:02.629 --> 11:04.429
â™ª <i>men.</i> â™ª

11:10.603 --> 11:11.803
Have you thought
this through?

11:11.805 --> 11:13.104
Having a kid
is a lot of work.

11:13.106 --> 11:16.374
Having you is
a lot of work.

11:16.376 --> 11:18.677
You know, having a child
would give my life meaning.

11:18.679 --> 11:20.211
Otherwise, all this
has been for nothing,

11:20.213 --> 11:21.713
And that's difficult
to accept.

11:21.715 --> 11:22.947
